\i0\b \cf0 \
Preliminaries:\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1940\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li1040\ql\qnatural

\b0 \cf0 TeXShop is a Mac OS X program which can typeset TeX and Latex files and preview the output on the screen. The program typesets using 
\i pdftex
\i0  or 
\i pdflatex
\i0  instead of 
\i tex
\i0  or 
\i latex
\i0 ; these programs output pdf files rather than dvi files. Since pdf is the native graphics format of Mac OS X, it is easy to display the output on the screen. 
\i Pdftex
\i0  and 
\i pdflatex
\i0  were written by  Han The Thanh, Petr Sojka, and Jiri Zlatuska.\
\
The pdf files created by TeXShop are standard pdf files which can be given to other people and displayed on a variety of computer systems. For example, they can be displayed by Adobe Acrobat on Mac OS 9. \
\
TeXShop does not include TeX. Instead it uses the standard TeX distribution 
\i teTeX
\i0 , a wonderful collection of the entire suite of TeX programs, files, and utilities created by Thomas Esser. This collection (the standard version of TeX on Linux systems) has been compiled for Mac OS X. Instructions for obtaining it are given below.\
\
TeXShop is written in Cocoa and relies on the NSPDFImageRep class to display output files. This class is not complete as of the beta release of Mac OS X; the following ingredients are missing:\
\
	a) the class cannot interpret embedded fonts, so it substitutes standard \
	system fonts in displays.\
\
	b) the class cannot interpret embedded graphic objects, so it shows an\
	empty region where the graphic would be.\
\
\pard\tx1440\tx2180\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\li1480\fi-20\ql\qnatural
\cf0 To overcome these restrictions, TeXShop contains a preference item instructing the program to image the pdf output using the unix program 
\i ghostscript
\i0 . Ghostscript is a program written by L. Peter Deutsch to manipulate postscript and pdf files; it often used on Linux systems. The program has been compiled for Mac OS X by John Hornkvist. Instructions for obtaining it are given below.\
\
Ghostscript is able to display TeX fonts and jpg images on the screen. The quality of the image obtained from ghostscript is not as high as the quality obtained from NSPDFImageRep, but it is sufficient to make the program useable. As soon as Apple completes NSPDFImageRep, the ghostscript preference item can be turned off and the current binary should work correctly.\
\pard\tx560\tx1940\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li1040\ql\qnatural

\b \cf0 \
Getting and Installing teTex:\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1940\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li1040\ql\qnatural

\b0 \cf0 The full teTeX distribution compiled for Mac OS X is available at the teTeX web site:\
\
	http://www.tug.org/tetex\
\
Several tar files must be obtained and installed, as explained at the site.\
\
Later versions of the distribution can be obtained and installed at any time; TeXShop does not install any configuration files in the teTeX tree.\
\
There is another way to obtain the distribution which is somewhat easier, and I'll give complete instructions for that method. Go to the TeXShop web site\
\
	http://www.uoregon.edu/~koch/texshop.texshop.html\
\
and click on the "teTeX" link to download the file "teTeX-full-1.0.2a-P-b.tgz.tar.gz". This is\
a 38.8 meg file.\
\
In a terminal window, type the command\
\
	gzip -d teTeX-full-1.0.2a-P-b.tgz.tar.gz\
\
and then the command\
\
	gnutar -xf teTeX-full-1.0.2a-P-b.tgz.tar\
\
These will produce a file titled teTeX-full.pkg with an icon showing an open box (together with a file "teTeX-full-1.0.2a-P-b.tgz.tar", which can be thrown away). The file teTeX-full.pkg is a package file which is recognized by the installer. 
\i However, the installer will not install in the correct spot,  so do not double click this file.
\i0 \
\
Log out and log in as 
\i root
\i0 . In a terminal window, type the following commands to create the directory "/Local/Library":\
\
	cd /\
	mkdir Local\
	cd Local\
	mkdir Library\
\
Drag the file teTeX-full.pkg to the directory /Local/Library.  Then type the following commands in a terminal window:\
\
	cd /Local/Library/teTeX-full.pkg\
	mv teTeX-full.pax.gz  /Local/Library\
	cd /Local/Library\
	gzip -d teTeX-full.pax.gz\
	pax -r -f teTeX-full.pax\
\
This will create a new folder named "teTeX" inside the folder "/Local/Library". The file "teTeX-full.pax" can be thrown away. The folder teTeX contains the complete teTeX distribution.\
\
While still logged in as 
\i root
\i0 , create symbolic links to the binary files for teTeX in the following manner. Create the directory "/usr/local/bin" if it does not exist. In a terminal window, type and execute the command\
\
	ln    -s    /Local/Library/teTeX/bin/powerpc-apple-rhapsody5.3/*    /usr/local/bin \
\
When you are done, log out and log in as yourself. You can immediately use the standard command line programs in TeX: 
\i tex, latex, dvips,
\i0  etc.\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1940\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li1040\ql\qnatural

